500 g Ground Beef
100 g Bacon Strips
2 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
3 unit(s) Russet Potato
½ cup White Cheddar Cheese, shredded
28 g Crispy Shallots
1 tbsp Worcestershire Sauce
4 tbsp Ketchup
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
28 g Spring Mix
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
45 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
1 tbsp Oil*
0.37 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch wedges.
Add potatoes, half the Zesty Garlic Spice Blend and 1 tbsp oil to a parchment-lined baking sheet. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, use 2 lined baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden-brown, 23-25 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, roast in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Meanwhile, a rrange bacon strips in a single layer on another parchment-lined baking sheet.
Roast bacon in the bottom of the oven until crispy and cooked through, 8-12 min.**
Transfer to paper-towel-lined plate.

Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.
Add beef, breadcrumbs, Worcestershire, remaining Zesty Garlic Spice Blend, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) pepper to a large bowl.
Form beef mixture into four equal-sized balls (eight for 4 pp).
Place patties on the prepared baking sheet. Place another piece of parchment over top.
Using a spatula or heavy-bottom pan, flatten balls into 1/2-inch-thick, 5-inch-wide patties.

Add burgers to one side of the grill. Reduce heat to medium, close lid and grill burgers, until cooked through, flipping once, 4-5 min per side.**
Remove from grill, then cover to keep warm.
When patties are almost finished, add bun halves, cut-side down, to other side of grill. Close lid and grill until buns are lightly toasted, 2-3 min.
Transfer patties and buns to clean baking sheet. Cover patties to keep warm.

Once burgers are finished, uncover, then top with cheese. Cook, patties in the top of the oven until cheese melts, 3-4 min.
Meanwhile, add half the ketchup and half the mayo to a small bowl. Stir together, then season with salt and pepper, to taste.
Set aside.

Spread remaining mayo on the bottom buns. Stack pickles, spring mix, one patty, half the crispy shallots, another patty, remaining crispy shallots and bacon.
Spread remaining ketchup over top buns, then place on burger.
Divide burgers and potatoes between plates. Serve fry sauce on the side for dipping.